definition.value: A double-positive thymocyte that is undergoing positive selection, has high expression of the alpha-beta T cell receptor, is CD69-positive, and is in the process of down regulating the CD4 co-receptor.
A CD4-positive, CD8-negative thymocyte that is CD24-positive and expresses high levels of the alpha-beta T cell receptor.
Described in the immgene database as being CD24-intermediate.
A CD4-positive, CD8-negative thymocyte that expresses high levels of the alpha-beta T cell receptor and is CD69-positive.
A CD8-positive, CD4-negative thymocyte that is CD24-positive and expresses high levels of the alpha-beta T cell receptor.
Described in the immgene database as being CD24-intermediate.
A CD4-positive, CD8-negative thymocyte that expresses high levels of the alpha-beta T cell receptor and is CD69-positive.
A mature CD4-positive, CD8-negative alpha-beta T cell found in the thymus that is CD24-low and has high expression of the T cell receptor.
A mature CD8-positive, CD4-negative alpha-beta T cell found in the thymus that is CD24-low and has high expression of the T cell receptor.
A mature NK cell that is NK1.1-positive.
Note: Nk1.1 expression is restricted to C57BL strains of laboratory mice.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is NKGA2-positive.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is Ly49D-positive.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is CD94-positive.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is CD94-negative and Ly49Cl-negative.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is Ly49Cl-positive.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is Ly49H-positive.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is Ly49D-negative.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is Ly49Cl-negative.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is CD94-negative.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is Ly49H-negative.
A NK1.1-positive T cell that is CD94-positive and Ly49Cl-positive.
A thymocyte that lacks expression of CD4 and CD8.
A T cell that is located in the intestinal epithelium and is capable of a mucosal immune response.

label.value: Vgamma5-positive CD8alpha alpha positive gamma-delta intraepithelial T cell

definition.value: A CD8alpha alpha positive gamma-delta intraepithelial T cell that expresses a TCR encoded in part by the Vgamma5 gene segment.

label.value: Vgamma5-negative CD8alpha alpha positive gamma-delta intraepithelial T cell

definition.value: A CD8alpha alpha positive gamma-delta intraepithelial T cell that does not express a TCR partially encoded by the Vgamma5 gene segment.
A regulatory T cell that has not encountered antigen.
This cell type has been described as CD45RA-negative, but this doesn't fit with our current definition of naive T cell.
A CD4-positive, CD25-positive alpha-beta regulatory T cell that has encountered antigen.
Cell has been described as being CD45RA-positive in human, but this doesn't fit with our current definition memory T cell.

A lymphocyte found in adipose tissue that lacks lineage markers of other lymphocytes but is capable of mediating TH2 cytokine responses. This cell type is found in fat associated lymphoid clusters, proliferates in response to IL2 and produce large amounts of TH2 cytokines such as IL5, IL6 and IL13
Any germinal center B cell that is part of a tonsil.
A large, granular, liver specific natural killer cell that adheres to the endothelial cells of the hepatic sinusoid.
Pit cells are named for the presence of large cytoplasmic granules that resemble pits (pips) of fruit.
May appear on a map.
A cavity developed along a bedding-plane and elongate in cross-section as a result.
Mine tailings are the materials left over after the process of separating the valuable fraction from the uneconomic fraction (gangue) of an ore.
A primary administrative division of a country, such as a state in the United States.
A subdivision of a first-order administrative division.
A subdivision of a second-order administrative division.
A subdivision of a third-order administrative division.
A political association with effective dominion over a geographic area.
A man-made feature constructed for the purpose of enabling the movement of humans, their animals or their vehicles.
An enclosure for displaying selected plant or animal life.
A geographical feature associated with water.
A collection of caves interconnected by enterable passages or linked hydrologically or a cave with an extensive complex of chambers and passages.
Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used for navigation, drainage or irrigation.
Continuous saline-water bodies that surround the continents and fill the Earth's great depressions.
A large expanse of saline water usually connected with an ocean.
A geographical feature associated with water with a halinity above 30 ppt (roughly 35 g/L).
A river that has either permanently or temporally lost its water.
A lake whose water contains a considerable concentration of dissolved salts.
A body of water or other liquid of considerable size contained on a body of land.
